statements.statementText:
f) Be able to determine, for 3-D surfaces given in the form z = f(x, y), the nature of maxima, minima and saddle-points by means of the sign of the determinant of the matrix of second partial derivatives (the Hessian Matrix),

H = [ f_{xx}  f_{xy} ]
    [ f_{yx}  f_{yy} ]

namely, that:
1. if H > 0 and f_{xx} > 0, there is a (local) minimum;
2. if H > 0 and f_{xx} < 0, there is a (local) maximum;
3. if H < 0 there is a saddle-point;
4. if H = 0 then the nature of the stationary point cannot be determined by this test.

